- = file
d = directory 
r = read permissions
w = write permissions
x = execute permissions


1st group - owner of the file 
2nd group - permission of the group that own the file 
3rd group - all other users .

example = (drwxr-xr-x)

chmod - change mode of the file 
+ =  add permission to the file
777 = god mode for file 

give user acces to files run - chown (username) (file)

adduser = adds new user

cat /etc/shadow - displays hashed passwords for users. 

su = switch user 

sudo passwd root

in order to give permissions to other users to change file permission you need to have them in the sudoers file.
